data.enText: a pig, especially one that is kept and made fat for eating
a male pig that has been castrated (= had part of its sex organs removed) and is kept for its meat

data.chText: 彻底地做某事；贯彻到底
data.enText: to do sth thoroughly or completely
to use or keep most of sth yourself and stop others from using or having it
to hog the road (= to drive so that other vehicles cannot pass)
to hog the bathroom (= to spend a long time in it so that others cannot use it)

data.chText: 彻底地做某事；贯彻到底
data.enText: to do sth thoroughly or completely

tr: a sheep up to the age of one year
a person regarded as greedy and pig-like

value.def: A hog is a pig. In British English, hog usually refers to a large male pig that has been castrated, but in American English it can refer to any kind of pig.

example.ex: We picked the corn by hand and we fed it to the hogs and the cows...
example.tran: 我们用手掰下玉米，把它喂给猪和牛吃。

example.ex: Johnny Warrick has a hog farm in Alabama.
example.tran: 约翰尼·沃里克在亚拉巴马州有个养猪场。

value.tran: 猪（英国英语中常指阉公猪，而美国英语中泛指猪）

value.def: If you hog something, you take all of it in a greedy or impolite way.

example.ex: Have you done hogging the bathroom?...
example.tran: 你要把浴室霸占到什么时候？

example.ex: Now, Bert, quit hogging the limelight.

value.def: If you go the whole hog, you do something bold or extravagant in the most complete way possible.

example.ex: Well, I thought, I've already lost half my job, I might as well go the whole hog and lose it completely.
example.tran: 嗯，我想，反正我的工作已经丢了一半了，干脆一不做二不休，走人算了。

value.tran: 彻底地干;一不做二不休
